claim: Campania was unaffected by the culture, government, and religion of the ancient Greeks and Romans.
premise_source_doc_sentence: The Greco-Roman world , Greco-Roman culture , or the term Greco-Roman  (  -LSB- ˌɡrɛkoʊˈroʊmən -RSB- or -LSB- ˌɡrɛkəˈroʊmən -RSB- spelled Graeco-Roman in the United Kingdom and the Commonwealth  )  , when used as an adjective , as understood by modern scholars and writers , refers to those geographical regions and countries that culturally  (  and so historically  )  were directly , long-term , and intimately influenced by the language , culture , government and religion of the ancient Greeks and Romans  (  including the Byzantine and Western Roman Empires  )  .
